description: India remembered Ratan Tata on his 88th birth anniversary with tributes from political leaders and industrialists. Tata Trusts highlighted his strategic philanthropic approach, while leaders praised his integrity, compassion, and role in reshaping Indian enterprise. His legacy of innovation, trust, and nation-building continues to inspire.
title: Ratan Tata's 88 birth anniversary: Politicians, industrialists pay tributes

author: KRISHNA CHAUDHARY
description: A Christmas night celebration turned violent in Bareilly when a woman was allegedly struck on the head with a glass bottle during an argument over a table at a club. The incident, captured on video, saw the woman assaulted by a group of men. Police have registered an FIR and are reviewing CCTV footage to apprehend the accused.
title: UP club brawl: Woman attacked with 'beer' bottle during Christmas celebration

author: TOI SCIENCE DESK
description: Earth's days are slowly getting longer. This change is driven by the Moon's gravity and shifts in Earth's mass due to melting ice and rising seas. Scientists use advanced tools to measure these tiny shifts. A 25-hour day is a distant future event, taking millions of years. The current changes are imperceptible.
title: Will Earth really switch to 25 hours days as its rotation slowing down

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: Microbiologist Dr. Shweta revealed the hidden fungal colonies thriving on money by culturing it in a lab.  Her findings highlight how everyday cash, passed through many hands, becomes a breeding ground for microbes.  This underscores the importance of diligent hand hygiene to prevent the spread of potential infections.
title: Your wallet isn’t as clean as you think: What a microbiologist found living on money

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: A 24-year-old MBA student from Tripura, Anjel Chakma, tragically died in Dehradun after a brutal stabbing, reportedly triggered by racial abuse. He was attacked on December 9th. The incident has sparked outrage and calls for justice, with authorities intensifying efforts to apprehend the main absconding accused.
title: Dehradun racial abuse: Tripura student stabbed to death; was called ‘chinki’, ‘momo’

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Arrogance is a career killer, according to Cisco's Sarah Walker, who prioritizes personality and a willingness to learn over experience.  She believes humility and continuous development are crucial for advancement at all levels.  Walker emphasizes that positive attitude and energy are unteachable qualities, making them invaluable in hiring.  Growth potential trumps current skills for success.
title: Cisco's top exec's hiring tip: No matter junior or senior, avoid this one trait

author: A SELVARAJ
description: Two residents died and over 10 were hospitalized in Karlambakkam Colony, Tiruvallur district, with symptoms of vomiting and diarrhea. Angry residents suspect contaminated drinking water and staged a highway blockade. Authorities are investigating the cause, with initial reports suggesting other factors for the deaths.
title: Deaths spark water contamination protest: Two die, over 10 hospitalised; probe under way

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Pakistan international kabaddi player Ubaidullah Rajput has been indefinitely banned by the Pakistan Kabaddi Federation for playing for an Indian team in a private tournament in Bahrain without a no-objection certificate. Rajput claimed it was a misunderstanding, but the federation cited his participation and representation of an Indian team as violations.
title: Pakistan kabaddi player wears Indian jersey, waves tricolour; banned indefinitely

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: A powerful winter storm battered the US Northeast and Great Lakes, causing widespread travel chaos with over 9,000 flights cancelled or delayed. Major transport hubs, particularly in the New York metropolitan area, experienced significant disruptions. States of emergency were declared as snow and ice created treacherous road conditions, impacting peak post-Christmas travel.
title: US snowstorm chaos: Over 9,000 flights hit; emergency orders in New York, New Jersey

author: TOI NEWS DESK
title: 'We can learn': Tharoor’s 'discipline' retort to Digvijaya Singh’s RSS praise

author: TNN
description: Bengaluru police have mandated that New Year's Eve celebrations at commercial establishments must conclude by 1 am. Venues are prohibited from exceeding their holding capacity and must close entry once full, with no waiting allowed outside. Offensive songs and slogans are banned, and security measures including screening and fire safety are compulsory.
title: New Year's in Bengaluru: Parties must end by 1am; check rules

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Ukraine faced a severe Russian aerial assault on Kyiv, killing at least two and injuring dozens, just hours before President Zelenskyy's crucial diplomatic meeting with US President Trump. The strikes, described by Zelenskyy as Moscow's response to peace efforts, highlight the ongoing conflict as Ukraine prepares to present a revised peace plan to Trump.
title: ‘A man of war’: Russia pounds Ukraine; high-stakes Trump–Zelenskyy talks in focus — 10 key points

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Rail traffic on the crucial Howrah–Patna–Delhi route faced significant disruption late Saturday night after eight wagons of a goods train derailed in Bihar's Jamui district. Fortunately, no injuries were reported. The incident, occurring between Lahabon and Simultala stations, affected approximately two dozen trains overnight. Restoration efforts are currently underway.
title: Bihar: 8 wagons of goods train derail, disrupt Howrah–Patna–Delhi rail route

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: A massive natural gas pipeline rupture in Castaic, Los Angeles County, triggered shelter-in-place orders and shut down Interstate 5. Residents reported loud booms and shaking homes, with social media showing large plumes of smoke. While the cause is under investigation, a mudslide is a possible factor. The highway has since reopened.
title: Gas line explosion rocks California: Video shows debris clouds filling the sky

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Power consumers could soon benefit from lower electricity bills as regulators review trading fees. This move coincides with the upcoming implementation of market coupling, a reform designed to unify electricity prices across trading platforms. The aim is to enhance efficiency and transparency, ultimately reducing procurement costs for buyers.
title: Lower electricity prices? CERC reviews power trading fee to ease cost

author: TIMESOFINDIA.COM
title: Mann Ki Baat: PM Modi highlights India's achievement in 2025 - key quotes

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Popular OTT series are significantly influencing travel choices, driving a surge in bookings to northeastern Indian cities like Imphal and Agartala. This screen-inspired wanderlust is transforming into tangible travel demand, as the region's landscapes and culture gain mainstream attention.  The trend highlights the growing impact of entertainment on travel decisions.
title: More tickets to the Northeast please! Did OTT boost regional tourism? What report says

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Ryan Rickelton's stunning 113 went in vain as MI Cape Town fell short by 15 runs in a high-scoring SA20 opener. Durban's Super Giants posted a record 232/5, powered by Devon Conway's 64, before Ethan Bosch's crucial wickets sealed the win.
title: Rs 1.07 cr for a catch! Fan takes one-handed blinder, steals the show - WATCH

author: TNN
description: In a heart-wrenching incident, Suraj Shivanna from Bengaluru succumbed to despair and ended his life in a Nagpur hotel, mere days after his wife's unfortunate passing. Grappling with accusations of dowry harassment and the impending strain from his in-laws, Suraj and his relatives were attempting to escape when the incident occurred.
title: Hounded after wife's suicide, Bengaluru man drives 1000 km to kill self

author: SEHJAL GUPTA
description: Power couple Jake Paul and Jutta Leerdam boast a combined net worth of $205 million in 2025.  Paul's wealth stems from boxing and business ventures, while Leerdam's comes from Olympic speed skating and sponsorships. Both are actively pursuing their respective careers, with Paul recently engaging in high-profile boxing matches and Leerdam preparing for upcoming international events.
title: Jake Paul and Jutta Leerdam combined net worth in 2025

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: A total of 36 wickets fell in just 142 overs, including 20 on the opening day, with the contest wrapped up in the evening session of day two as England sealed a four-wicket win — their first Test victory in Australia since January 2011.
title: Ashes: 36 wickets in 2 days! MCG curator in 'state of shock'

author: TOI SCIENCE DESK
description: A vital ocean current system in the Atlantic is showing signs of instability. Scientists warn this could lead to colder winters and unpredictable weather patterns across Europe.  This gradual change, tracked through ancient shells, suggests a potential shift in climate.  Reducing greenhouse gas emissions is crucial to mitigate these risks and prevent irreversible changes to the climate system.
title: Could a North Atlantic current really change Europe’s climate into an ice age

author: SARANG DASTANE AND GITESH SHELKE
description: Arrested gangster Bandu Andekar and two relatives attempted to file nomination papers for the PMC polls but were unsuccessful due to missing documents. Despite court permission and police escort, they couldn't complete the process, causing disruptions for other candidates.
title: Hands tied, face covered: Why did a gangster's Pune civic polls nomination bid fail?

author: TOI NEWS DESK
title: ‘Nothing to learn’: How Cong reacted to Digvijaya Singh’s RSS praise; senior leader clarifies stance

author: TNN
description: The husband of a BJP corporator in Satna district has been booked for threatening and misbehaving with a woman. A viral video purportedly shows him threatening the woman, who claims he also made objectionable demands. Police have registered a case and apprehended the accused.
title: 'Nothing will happen to me': BJP corporator's husband accused of assault; detained after viral video

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Indian travelers are diversifying New Year destinations beyond Thailand and Cambodia due to border violence. Vietnam, Indonesia, Sri Lanka, Japan, and West Asia are gaining popularity. While Thailand sees a slight dip in bookings, Cambodia faces a stronger reaction. Rising airfares also influence choices, favoring shorter, visa-on-arrival destinations.
title: Thailand–Cambodia clashes: Indian tourists scout safer New Year destinations

author: BARSHA DUTTA
description: Chloe Kim shared heartfelt praise for Myles Garrett, saying she is inspired by his work ethic, kindness, and steady support. As she prepares for another Olympic season, the two-time gold medalist explained that their connection is built on respect, not fame. Kim said Garrett’s character and encouragement help her navigate pressure while staying grounded and focused.
title: 'I’m really lucky': Chloe Kim praises Myles Garrett’s support ahead of her Olympic return

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Amidst the harsh Chillai Kalan winter, the Army has intensified counter-terrorism operations in Jammu and Kashmir's Kishtwar and Doda districts.  Expanding into snowbound areas, forces are pursuing an estimated 30-35 Pakistani terrorists seeking winter hideouts. An integrated, proactive approach involving multiple agencies ensures continuous pressure and swift responses to intelligence.
title: 30–35 terrorists on radar: Army steps up counterterror ops in J&K; intense vigil amid 'Chillai Kalan'

author: TOI Education
description: The National Testing Agency has released an important advisory for CUET UG 2026 aspirants. The exam is scheduled for May 2026. Candidates must apply through the official NTA website. The advisory focuses on Aadhaar authentication and resolving name mismatches. Aspirants should regularly check NTA websites for updates on courses, universities, and the syllabus.
title: CUET UG 2026: NTA issues important advisory ahead of May exam; check details

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Delhi grappled with severe air pollution on Sunday, with smog obscuring landmarks like Akshardham Temple and reducing visibility across the city. Several areas recorded 'very poor' and 'severe' air quality, with AQI levels exceeding 400 in some parts. In contrast, Mumbai experienced moderate air quality with a light fog.
title: Delhi air pollution: AQI hits 391, city back in ‘severe’ category; Mumbai records 'moderate' 123

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Magnus Carlsen expressed frustration after a loss to Vladislav Artemiev at the World Rapid and Blitz Championships. Artemiev secured the victory with a decisive move, extending his lead in the tournament standings. Carlsen's defeat was followed by an irritated reaction to a cameraman.
title: Magnus Carlsen loses cool after defeat to Artemiev, pushes cameraman - Watch

author: RAUNAK BOSE
description: Los Angeles Lakers are reportedly in talks to reacquire Malik Monk from the Sacramento Kings. The proposed trade would send Gabe Vincent and Jarred Vanderbilt to Sacramento, potentially including rookie Devin Carter. This move aims to bolster the Lakers' bench scoring while offering the Kings financial flexibility and defensive reinforcement.
title: NBA trade rumor: Lakers predicted to bag $81 million Sacramento Kings power duo

author: AMIT KUMAR
description: Like Axar Patel, Jayswal hails from Nadiad in Gujarat’s Kheda district and began his cricket journey at the same academy where Team India’s T20I vice-captain took his first steps. Jayswal lost his father when he was just eight months old. As he grew older, cricket became his passion, and he told his mother of his dream to become a professional cricketer. The road was far from easy, but his mother stood firmly by him.
title: 'Opportunity aayega, mehnat kar': Virat Kohli to Jayswal

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Europe faces a critical choice: prioritize AI development or uphold strict climate goals. Analysts warn that stringent environmental regulations and energy constraints are hindering AI infrastructure growth, potentially causing Europe to miss out on a major technological wave. This dilemma intensifies as AI's energy demands surge, forcing a re-evaluation of climate commitments.
title: Compete or fall behind: Tesla Bull Dan Ives on Europe’s AI development ambitions

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Delhi's Environment Minister announced two permanent Graded Response Action Plan (GRAP-4) restrictions to combat severe air pollution. Vehicles will now require a valid Pollution Under Control Certificate (PUCC) to refuel, and non-BS6 compliant vehicles entering the city will be restricted. These measures aim to mitigate pollution-related hardships for residents.
title: 'No fuel without PUCC': Delhi to make two key GRAP-4 curbs permanent to fight pollution

author: TNN
description: JP Nagar police apprehended Mehaboob Khan Patan, a 38-year-old burglar. His night blindness compelled him to commit crimes only during daylight hours. Patan stole valuables worth Rs 65.2 lakh from actor Praveen Kumar M's residence. He confessed to multiple thefts across states. Recovered items include gold, silver, cash, and a two-wheeler. His arrest solved seven theft cases.
title: Bengaluru: Night-blind burglar strikes actor’s home, walks away with Rs 65-lakh booty

author: YUDHVIR RANA
description: A tandem paragliding pilot died in a crash shortly after takeoff at Bir Billing, marking the third fatality this year. The incident has raised concerns about safety standards and pilot working conditions. An inquiry is underway, with authorities emphasizing strict adherence to SOPs and passenger screening.
title: Paragliding pilot dies during takeoff at Bir Billing; tourist survives

author: RAJIV KALKOD
description: A husband was sentenced to life imprisonment for murdering his wife after she discovered a tattoo of another woman on his arm. He drugged her with sleeping pills mixed in beer, and when she survived, he strangled her. Circumstantial evidence, including CCTV footage and witness testimonies, led to his conviction.
title: Tattoo affair: Bengaluru man gets life term for murdering wife; strangled her when sleeping pills didn’t work

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Aditya Dhar's 'Dhurandhar' continues its phenomenal run, crossing Rs. 660 crore domestically and Rs. 1025 crore worldwide in its fourth week. Despite new releases, the film maintains its box office dominance.  Recent weekend collections show strong performance, with Saturday adding Rs. 20.50 crore to its impressive total.
title: ‘Dhurandhar’ collection day 23: Ranveer Singh starrer crosses Rs 1025cr mark worldwide

author: TNN
description: Cybercrime transcends borders, exploiting anonymity and human emotions like greed and fear, according to Special CP Devesh Chandra Srivastava.  He highlighted that even educated individuals fall prey to scams by understanding psychological triggers, emphasizing personal awareness as the primary defense against evolving threats like AI-driven frauds and deepfakes.
title: ‘Don't Get Scammed': Stop, think & then act before letting fear take over

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Former cricketer Navjot Singh Sidhu wants Virat Kohli to return to Test cricket.  Kohli retired from Tests in May 2025 after a successful career.  He continues to perform well in One Day Internationals.  Recent performances in Australia and South Africa show his enduring form.  This has led to calls for his Test comeback.
title: 'If God granted me a wish': Ex-cricketer makes emotional plea for Kohli's Test return

author: MAZHAR ALI
description: A Special Investigation Team in Chandrapur has uncovered a direct link to China in the illegal sale of a farmer's kidney. Interrogations revealed that a Chinese surgeon, Dr. Chiang, conducted transplants in Cambodia and supplied harvested organs to Chinese clients, including the kidney of a local farmer.
title: Maharashtra: SIT probe finds China link to kidney racket

author: ADVITYA BAHL
description: A criminal case has been filed against three doctors and health officials after a nearly half-meter surgical cloth was found inside a woman's abdomen over a year after her delivery. The foreign object, left during a C-section in November 2023, caused persistent pain and complications before its removal in April. The woman's husband alleges negligence and threats during the investigation.
title: Noida: Cloth found in woman’s abdomen 15 months after C-section; FIR against 6 doctors

author: PARAG DAVE AND TUSHAR TERE
description: A group of over 70 Indians, defying age and physical limitations, are embracing adventure. From skydiving and scuba diving to trekking in Antarctica, these seniors are living life to the fullest. Couples like the Kotharis, Thakors, and Vakils are proving that age is merely a number, prioritizing experiences and curiosity over potential hardships, with their bucket lists still growing.
title: Old & bold: When 70+ go skydiving & bungee jumping

author: REBECCA SAMERVEL
description: A 17-year-old domestic violence case took an unexpected turn when a woman's current husband testified, confirming her second marriage. This revelation led a Borivli court to rule she was no longer entitled to maintenance from her ex-husband, effectively ending her claim for protection and monetary relief initiated in 2009.
title: Twist in court: 2nd husband testifies for 1st; woman loses 17-year old DV case

author: ABHIJAY JHA
description: A National Green Tribunal-ordered inspection of Yamuna floodplains revealed large-scale violations by miners, including operating heavy machinery within the river's flow and exceeding legal lease boundaries. The joint committee's report highlighted administrative lapses and recommended urgent action against illegal mining and short-term leases.
title: Yamuna sand mining: Mid-river digs to illegal ramps, NGT panel finds major violations

author: GLOBAL SPORTS DESK
description: WWE icon The Boogeyman, Marty Wright, and actress Melissa George have a combined net worth of approximately $7 million as of 2025. George's acting career contributes the larger share, with both having diversified income streams from their respective entertainment fields. Their success reflects legacy, audience loyalty, and decades of creative labor.
title: The Boogeyman & Melissa George net worth 2025: WWE legacy and earnings

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Vijay Sales has launched its Apple Days Sale, running from December 28 to January 4, 2026, offering discounts on iPhones, MacBooks, iPads, and more across 160+ outlets and online. Customers can avail instant bank discounts, exchange bonuses up to Rs 10,000, and earn MyVS loyalty points. Special pricing is also available on demo and open units.
title: Vijay Sales Apple Days sale: iPhone 17 price starts at Rs 78,900; check details

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Google co-founder Sergey Brin shared a key lesson learned from the Google Glass failure, advising entrepreneurs to fully develop their ideas before public stunts. He admitted to rushing commercialization and aiming for a "Steve Jobs moment" prematurely.
title: 'Thought I was next Steve Jobs': Google founder shares lesson from early days
